obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (35168)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 1st July, 1955, vide notification No. S.R.O. 1077, dated 14th May, 1955, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35168&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the State Bank of India Act, 1955.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (35169)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35169&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date on which this Act comes into force;`
  line
  line `(b) "Central Board" means the Central Board of Directors of the State Bank;`
  line
  line `^1[(bb) "chairman" means the chairman of the Central Board;]`
  line
  line `(c) "goods" includes bullion, wares and merchandise;`
  line
  line `(d) "Imperial Bank" means the Imperial Bank of India constituted under the Imperial Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1920 (47 of 1920);`
  line
  line `^1[(dd) Local Board means a Local Board constituted under section 21;]`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(g) "State Bank" means the State Bank of India constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4[(j) "workman" has the meaning assigned to it in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947).]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 1964, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (h) omitted by Act 19 of 2018, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (35170)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of the State Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2007, s. 2, for "Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 29-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35170&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Bank to be called the State Bank of India shall be`
  line `constituted to carry on the business of banking and other business in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act and for the purpose of taking over the undertaking of the Imperial Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[Central Government], together with such other persons as may from time to time become`
  line `shareholders in the State Bank in accordance with the provisions of this Act, shall, so long as they are`
  line `shareholders in the State Bank, constitute a body corporate with perpetual succession and a common seal`
  line `under the name of the State Bank of India, and shall sue and be sued in that name.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Bank shall have power to acquire and hold property, whether movable or immovable,`
  line `for the purposes for which it is constituted and to dispose of the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35171)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Authorised capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 3, for section 4 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35171&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Authorised capital.--Subject to the provisions of this Act, the authorised capital of the State`
  line `Bank shall be five thousand crores of rupees divided into five hundred crores of fully paid-up shares often`
  line `rupees each:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Board may reduce the nominal or face value of the shares, and divide the`
  line `authorised capital into such denomination as it may decide with the approval of the Reserve Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, increase or`
  line `reduce the authorised capital so however that the shares in all cases shall be fully paid-up shares.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35172)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Issued capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35172&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The issued capital of the State Bank shall, on the appointed day, be five`
  line `crores, sixty-two lakhs and fifty thousand rupees divided into five lakhs, sixty-two thousand and five`
  line `hundred shares, all of which shall, on the appointed day, stand allotted to the Reserve Bank in lieu of the`
  line `shares of the Imperial Bank ^1[transferred to and vested in it under section 6].`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The issued capital of the State Bank shall consist of equity shares or equity and preference`
  line `shares:`
  line
  line `Provided that the issue of preference shares shall be in accordance with the guidelines framed by the`
  line `Reserve Bank specifying the class of preference shares, the extent of issue of each class of such`
  line `preference shares (whether perpetual or irredeemable or redeemable) and the terms and conditions subject`
  line `to which, each class of preference shares may be issued:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Board may from time to time increase, with the previous approval of`
  line `the Reserve Bank and the Central Government, whether by public issue or rights issue or preferential`
  line `allotment or private placement, in accordance with the procedure as may be prescribed, the issued capital`
  line `by the issue of equity or preference shares:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Central Government shall, at all times, hold not less than fifty-one per cent. of`
  line `the issued capital consisting of equity shares of the State Bank.]`
  line
  line `(3) No increase in the issued capital beyond twelve crores and fifty lakhs of rupees shall be made`
  line `under sub-section (2) without the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (2), the Central Board may increase from time`
  line `to time, by way of issuing bonus shares to existing equity shareholders, the issued capital in such manner`
  line `as the Central Government may, after consultation with the Reserve Bank, direct.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Bank may, accept the money in respect of shares issued towards increase in the issued`
  line `capital in instalments, make calls, forfeit unpaid shares and re-issue them, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1955, s. 2, for "transferred to it by paragraph 2 of the First Schedule" (w.e.f. 21-9-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 4, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35173)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Transfer of assets and liabilities of the Imperial Bank to the State Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1955, s. 3, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 21-9-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35173&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `other provisions contained in this Act, on the appointed day,--`
  line
  line `(a) all shares in the capital of the Imperial Bank shall be transferred to, and shall vest in, the`
  line `Reserve Bank, free of all trusts, liabilities and encumbrances, and`
  line
  line `(b) the undertaking of the Imperial Bank shall be transferred to, and shall vest in, the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) The undertaking of the Imperial Bank shall be deemed to include all rights, powers, authorities`
  line `and privileges, and all property, movable and immovable, including cash balances, reserve funds,`
  line `investments and all other interests and rights in, or arising out of, such property as may be in the`
  line `possession of that bank immediately before the appointed day, and all books, accounts, and documents`
  line `relating thereto, and shall also be deemed to include all debts, liabilities and obligations of whatever kind`
  line `then existing of that bank.`
  line
  line `^1 [(3) Unless otherwise expressly provided by or under this Act, all contracts, deeds, bonds,`
  line `agreements, powers of attorney, grants of legal representation and other instruments of whatever nature`
  line `subsisting or having effect immediately before the appointed day and to which the Imperial Bank is a`
  line `party or which are in favour of the Imperial Bank shall be of as full force and effect against or in favour of`
  line `the State Bank, as the case may be, and may be enforced or acted upon as fully and effectually as if`
  line `instead of the Imperial Bank the State Bank had been a party thereto or as if they had been issued in`
  line `favour of the State Bank].`
  line
  line `(4) If on the appointed day any suit, appeal or other legal proceeding of whatever nature, is pending`
  line `by or against the Imperial Bank, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be in any way prejudicially`
  line `affected by reason of the transfer to the State Bank of the undertaking of the Imperial Bank or of anything`
  line `contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted and enforced`
  line `by or against the State Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35174)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Transfer of service of existing officers and employees of the Imperial Bank to the State Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35174&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer or other employee of the Imperial Bank (excepting the managing director, the`
  line `deputy managing director and other directors) in the employment of the Imperial Bank immediately`
  line `before the appointed day shall, on and from the appointed day, become an officer or other employee, as`
  line `the case may be, of the State Bank, and shall hold his office or service therein by the same tenure, at the`
  line `same remuneration and upon the same terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to`
  line `pension, gratuity and other matters as he would have held the same on the appointed day if the`
  line `undertaking of the Imperial Bank had not vested in the State Bank, and shall continue to do so unless and`
  line `until his employment in the State Bank is terminated or until his remuneration, terms or conditions are`
  line `duly altered by the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who, on the appointed day, is entitled to or is in receipt of, a pension or other`
  line `superannuation or compassionate allowance or benefit from the Imperial Bank or any provident, pension`
  line `or other fund or any authority administering such fund shall be entitled to be paid by, and to receive from,`
  line `the State Bank or any provident, pension or other fund or any authority administering such fund the same`
  line `pension, allowance or benefit so long as he observes the conditions on which the pension, allowance or`
  line `benefit was granted, and if any question arises whether he has so observed such conditions, the question`
  line `shall be determined by the Central Government and the decision of the Central Government thereon shall`
  line `be final.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), no appointment made or`
  line `promotion, increment in salary, pension, allowance or any other benefit granted to any person after the`
  line `19th day of December, 1954, and before the appointed day which would not ordinarily have been made or`
  line `granted or which would not ordinarily have been admissible under the rules or authorisations of the`
  line `Imperial Bank or of any provident, pension or other fund in force prior to the 19th day of December, 1954, shall have effect or be payable or claimable from the State Bank or from any provident, pension or`
  line `other fund or from any authority administering the fund, unless the Central Government has, by general or`
  line `special order, confirmed the appointment, promotion or increment or has directed the continued grant of`
  line `the pension allowance or other benefit as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other employes of the`
  line `Imperial Bank from that Bank to the State Bank shall not entitle such officer or other employees to any`
  line `compensation under that Act or other law, and no such claim shall be entertained by any Court, Tribunal`
  line `or other authority.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person holding office as managing director, deputy managing director, director or member of`
  line `any Local Board of the Imperial Bank immediately before the appointed day shall be deemed to have`
  line `vacated his office as such on the appointed day, and notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force or in any agreement or contract, he shall not be entitled to any`
  line `compensation from the Imperial Bank or the State Bank for the loss of office or for the premature`
  line `termination of any agreement or contract relating to his employment, except such pension, compensation`
  line `or other benefit which the State Bank may grant to him, having regard to what that person would have`
  line `received as an officer of the Imperial Bank if this Act had not been passed and if he had retired from his`
  line `employment in the ordinary course.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any managing director, deputy managing director, director, officer or other employee of`
  line `the Imperial Bank has, after the 19th day of December, 1954, and before the appointed day, been paid any`
  line `sum by way of compensation or gratuity, the State Bank shall be entitled to claim refund of any sum so`
  line `paid if the payment is not confirmed by the Central Government by general or special order.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (35175)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Existing provident and other funds of the Imperial Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35175&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `For the persons who immediately`
  line `before the appointed day are the trustees of the following funds, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Imperial Bank of India Employees Provident Fund;`
  line
  line `(b) the Imperial Bank of India Employees Pension and Guarantee Fund;`
  line
  line `(c) the Bank of Bombay Officers Pension and Guarantee Fund;`
  line
  line `(d) the Bank of Madras Pension and Gratuity Fund; and`
  line
  line `(e) the Bank of Madras Officers Provident and Mutual Guarantee Fund;`
  line
  line `there shall be substituted as trustees such persons as the Central Government may, by general or special`
  line `order, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (35176)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Compensation to be given to shareholders of Imperial Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35176&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who`
  line `immediately before the appointed day is registered as a holder of shares in the Imperial Bank shall be`
  line `entitled to compensation in accordance with the provisions contained in the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect the rights inter se between the holder of any`
  line `share in the Imperial Bank and any other person who may have an interest in such share, and such other`
  line `person shall be entitled to enforce his interest against the compensation awarded to the holder of such`
  line `share, but not against the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (35177)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Transferability of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35177&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), the shares of the`
  line `State Bank shall be freely transferable.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall entitle the ^1[Central Government] to transfer any shares`
  line `held by it in the State Bank if such transfer will result in reducing the shares held by it to less than ^2[fifty-one per cent. of the issued capital consisting of equity shares,] of the State Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2007, s. 4, for "Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 29-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by 27 of 2010, s. 5, for "fifty-five per cent. of the issued capital" (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (35178)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Right of registered shareholders to nominate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 6 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35178&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Right of registered shareholders to nominate.--(1) Every individual registered shareholder`
  line `may, at any time, nominate, in the prescribed manner, an individual to whom all his rights in the shares`
  line `shall vest in the event of his death.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the shares are registered in the name of more than one individual jointly, the joint holders`
  line `may together nominate in the prescribed manner, an individual to whom all their rights in the shares shall`
  line `vest in the event of the death of all the joint holders.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any`
  line `disposition, whether testamentary or otherwise, where a nomination in respect of shares is made in the`
  line `prescribed manner and which purports to confer on the nominee the right to vest the shares, the nominee`
  line `shall, on the death of the shareholder or, as the case may be, on the death of all the joint holders, become`
  line `entitled to all the rights of the shareholder or, as the case may be, of all the joint holders, in relation to`
  line `such shares and all other persons shall be excluded unless the nomination is varied or cancelled in the`
  line `prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the nominee is a minor, it shall be lawful for the individual registered holder of the shares`
  line `to make nomination to appoint, in the prescribed manner, any person to become entitled to the shares in`
  line `the event of his death during the minority of the nominee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (35179)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Restrictions on voting rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35179&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Restrictions on voting rights.--No shareholder, other than the ^2[Central Government], shall be`
  line `entitled to exercise voting rights in respect of any shares held by him in excess of ten per cent. of the`
  line `issued capital:`
  line
  line `Provided that such shareholder shall be entitled to exercise voting rights at such higher percentage as`
  line `the Central Government may, after consultation with the ^2[Central Government], specify.]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that the shareholder holding any preference share capital in the State Bank shall, in`
  line `respect of such capital, have a right to vote only on resolutions placed before the State Bank which`
  line `directly affect the rights attached to his preference shares:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no preference shareholder, other than the Central Government, shall be entitled to`
  line `exercise voting rights in respect of preference shares held by him in excess of ten per cent, of total voting`
  line `rights of all the shareholders holding preference share capital only.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 3, for section 11 (15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2007, s. 5, for "Reserve Bank" (w.e.f. 29-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (35180)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Shares to be approved securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 4, for "Banking Companies, 1949" (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35180&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Acts hereinafter`
  line `mentioned in this section, the shares of the State Bank shall be deemed to be included among the`
  line `securities enumerated in section 20 of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882), and also to be approved`
  line `securities for the purposes of the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938), and the ^1[Banking Regulations Act,`
  line `1949 (10 of 1949)].`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (35181)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Register of shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35181&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[13. Register of shareholders.--(1) The State Bank shall keep at its Central Office, a register, in`
  line `one or more books of the shareholders, and shall enter therein the following particulars so far as they may`
  line `be available:--`
  line
  line `(i) the names, addresses and occupations, if any, of the shareholders and a statement of the shares`
  line `held by each shareholder, distinguishing each share by its denoting number;`
  line
  line `(ii) the date on which each person is so entered as a shareholder;`
  line
  line `(iii) the date on which any person ceases to be a shareholder; and`
  line
  line `(iv) such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to the shares held with a depository.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the State Bank to`
  line `keep the register of shareholders ^3[in computer floppies or diskettes or any other electronic form] subject`
  line `to such safeguards as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), a copy of, or`
  line `extract from, the register of shareholders, certified to be a true copy under the hand of an officer of the`
  line `State Bank authorised in this behalf, shall, in all legal proceedings, be admissible in evidence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for section 13 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 8 of 1997, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-1-1997).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 8, for "in computer floppies or diskettes" (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (35182)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 15
  title `Register of beneficial owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1997, s. 4 (w.e.f. 15-1-1997).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35182&sectionno=13A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Register of beneficial owners.-- The register of beneficial owners maintained by a depository`
  line `under section 11 of the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996), shall be deemed to be a register of`
  line `shareholders for the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (42833)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=42833&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `[Branch registers.]Omitted by the State Bank of India (Amendment) Act, 1993 (3 of 1994), s. 6`
  line `(w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (42834)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Trusts not to be entered on the register of shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=42834&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Trusts not to be entered on the register of shareholders.--No notice of any trust, express,`
  line `implied or constructive, shall be entered on the register of shareholders or be receivable by the State`
  line Bank.]
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a depository in respect of shares held by it as a`
  line `registered owner on behalf of the beneficial owners.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of section 13, section 13A and this section, the expressions`
  line `"beneficial owner", "depository" and "registered owner" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in clauses (a), (e) and (j) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996).]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1993, s. 7, for section 15 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso and Explanation ins. by Act 8 of 1997, s. 5 (w.e.f. 15-1-1997).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (35184)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Offices, branches and agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35184&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise provided by the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, the Central Office of the State Bank shall be at ^1[Mumbai, and shall`
  line `also be known as Corporate Centre].`
  line
  line `(2) The State Bank shall have local head offices in^2[Mumbai, Kolkata and Chennai] and at such other`
  line `places in India as the Central Government, in consultation with the Central Board, may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Bank shall maintain as its branches or agencies, all branches or agencies of the Imperial`
  line `Bank which were in existence ^3[in India] immediately before the appointed day, and no such branch may`
  line `be closed without the previous approval of the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Bank may establish branches or agencies at any place in or outside India in addition to`
  line `the branches or agencies referred to in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4), the State Bank shall establish not less than`
  line `four hundred branches in addition to the branches referred to in sub-section (3) within five years of the`
  line `appointed day or such extended period as the Central Government may specify in this behalf, and the`
  line `places where such additional branches are to be established shall be determined in accordance with any`
  line `such programme as may be drawn up by the Central Government from time to time in consultation with`
  line `the Reserve Bank and the State Bank, and no branch so established shall be closed without the previous`
  line `approval of the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 9, for Bombay (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "Bombay, Calcutta and Madras" (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 33 of 1955, s. 4 (w.e.f. 21-9-1955).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (35185)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title Management.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35185&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence and direction of the affairs and business of the`
  line `State Bank shall be entrusted to the Central Board which may exercise all powers and do all such acts and`
  line `things as may be exercised or done by the State Bank and are not by this Act expressly directed or`
  line `required to be done by the State Bank in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Board in discharging its functions shall act on business principles, regard being had to`
  line `public interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (35186)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Central Board to be guided by directions of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35186&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the discharge of its`
  line `functions ^1*** the State Bank shall be guided by such directions in matters of policy involving public`
  line `interest as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Governor of the Reserve Bank and the`
  line `chairman of the State Bank, give to it.`
  line
  line `(2) ^2[All directions shall be given by the Central Government] and, if any question arises whether a`
  line `direction relates to a matter of policy involving public interest, the decision of the Central Government`
  line `thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "including those relating to a subsidiary bank" omitted by Act 19 of 2018, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2007, s. 6, for "All directions given by the Central Government shall be given through the Reserve Bank"`
  line `(w.e.f. 29-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (35187)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Composition of the Central Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35187&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1*** The Central Board shall consist of the following,`
  line `namely:`
  line
  line `(a) a chairman ^2*** to be appointed by the Central Government in consultation with the Reserve`
  line `Bank ^3***.`
  line
  line `^4[(b) such number of managing directors not exceeding four, as may be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Reserve Bank;]`
  line
  line ^5*****
  line
  line `(c) if the total amount of the holdings of the shareholders, other than the ^6[Central Government],`
  line `whose names are on the ^7[register of shareholders] three months before the date fixed for election of`
  line `directors is--`
  line
  line `(i) not more than ten per cent. of the total issued capital, two directors,`
  line
  line `(ii) more than ten per cent. but not more than twenty-five per cent. of such capital three`
  line `directors, and`
  line
  line `(iii) more than twenty-five per cent. of such capital, four directors, to be elected in the`
  line `prescribed manner by such shareholders;`
  line
  line `^8[(ca) one director, from among the employees of the State Bank, who are workmen, to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government in the manner provided in the rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(cb) one director, from among such of the employees of the State Bank, as are not workmen, to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government in the manner provided in the rules made under this Act];`
  line
  line `(d) not less than two and not more than six directors to be nominated by the Central`
  line `Government, ^9*** from among persons having special knowledge of the working of co-operative`
  line `institutions and of rural economy or experience in commerce, industry, banking or finance;]`
  line
  line `(e) one director to be nominated by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `^10[(f) one director, possessing necessary expertise and experience in matters relating to regulation`
  line `or supervision of commercial banks to be nominated by the Central Government on the`
  line `recommendation of the Reserve Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets and figure "(1)" omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Certain words omitted by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `3. The words "and a vice-chairman" omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2007, s. 7, for ''Reserve Bank'' (w.e.f. 29-6-2007).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 8, for ''Principal register'' (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line
  line `9. The words ''in consultation with the Reserve Bank'' omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for clause (f) (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (35188)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 22
  title `Qualifications for election of directors elected by shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 11 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35188&sectionno=19A&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[19A. Qualifications for election of directors elected by shareholders.--(1) The directors elected`
  line `under clause (c) of section 19 shall--`
  line
  line `(a) have special knowledge or experience in respect of one or more of the following areas,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) agriculture and rural economy,`
  line
  line `(ii) banking,`
  line
  line `(iii) co-operation,`
  line
  line `(iv) economics,`
  line
  line `(v) finance,`
  line
  line `(vi) law,`
  line
  line `(vii) small-scale industry,`
  line
  line `(viii) any other area the special knowledge of, and experience in, which in the opinion of the`
  line `Reserve Bank shall be useful to the State Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) represent the interests of depositors; or`
  line
  line `(c) represent the interests of farmers, workers and artisans.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1) and notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force, no person shall be eligible to`
  line `be elected as director under clause (c) of section 19 unless he is a person having fit and proper status`
  line `based upon track record, integrity and such other criteria as the Reserve Bank may notify from time to`
  line `time in this regard and the Reserve Bank may specify in the notification issued under this sub-section, the`
  line `authority to determine the fit and proper status, the manner of such determination, the procedure to be`
  line `followed for such determinations and such other matters as may be considered necessary or incidental`
  line thereto.
  line
  line `(3) Where the Reserve Bank is of the opinion that any director of the State Bank elected under clause`
  line `(c) of section 19 does not fulfil the requirements of sub-sections (1) and (2), it may, after giving to such`
  line `director and the State Bank a reasonable opportunity of being heard, by order, remove such director.`
  line
  line `(4) On the removal of a director under sub-section (3), the Central Board shall co-opt any other`
  line `person fulfilling the requirements of sub-sections (1) and (2), as a director in place of the person so`
  line `removed, till a director is duly elected by the shareholders of the State Bank in the next annual general`
  line `meeting; and the person so co-opted shall be deemed to have been duly elected by the shareholders of the`
  line `State Bank as a director.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_b:
  sectionId (35189)
  sectionNo 19B
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to appoint additional directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 11 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35189&sectionno=19B&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_19_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[19B. Power of Reserve Bank to appoint additional directors.--(1) If the Reserve Bank is of the`
  line `opinion that in the interest of banking policy or in the public interest or in the interests of the State Bank`
  line `or its depositors, it is necessary so to do, it may, from time to time and by order in writing appoint, with`
  line `effect from such date as may be specified in the order, one or more persons as additional directors of the`
  line `State Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person appointed as additional director under sub-section (1) shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office during the pleasure of the Reserve Bank and subject thereto for a period not`
  line `exceeding three years or such further periods not exceeding three years at a time as the Reserve Bank`
  line `may, by order, specify;`
  line
  line `(b) not incur any obligation or liability by reason only of his being an additional director or for`
  line `anything done or omitted to be done in good faith in the execution of the duties of his office or in`
  line `relation thereto; and`
  line
  line `(c) not be required to hold qualification shares in the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of reckoning any proportion of the total number of directors of the State Bank any`
  line `additional director appointed under this section shall not be taken into account.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (35190)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Term of office of chairman, managing director, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35190&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[The chairman, ^2*** and each`
  line `managing director] shall hold office for such term not exceeding five years, as the Central Government`
  line `may fix when appointing them and shall be eligible for reappointment.`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government shall have the`
  line `right to terminate the terms of office of the chairman, ^2*** or a managing director, as the case may be, at`
  line `any time before the expiry of the term fixed under sub-section (1) by giving him notice of not less than`
  line `three months in writing or three months' salary and allowances in lieu of such notice;`
  line `and the chairman, ^2*** or a managing director, as the case may be, shall also have the right to relinquish his office at any`
  line `time before the expiry of the term so fixed by giving to the Central Government notice of not less than`
  line `three months in writing.]`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions contained in section 19 and ^5*** a director elected under clause (c)`
  line ^6***
  line `of ^7[that section] shall hold office for ^8[three years] and ^9*** ^10 *** and shall be eligible for reelection ^11***:`
  line
  line `^12[Provided that no such director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years.]`
  line
  line `^13[(3A)`
  line `^14[subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (4), a director] appointed under clause`
  line `(ca) or clause (cb)`
  line `^15[of section 19 or nominated under clause (d) of that section] shall hold office for such`
  line `term, not exceeding three years, as the Central Government may specify ^16*** and shall be eligible ^17[for`
  line `re appointment or re-nomination, as the case may be:]]`
  line
  line `^12[Provided that no such director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years.]`
  line
  line `^18[(4) A director appointed under clause (ca) or clause (cb) ^19[of section 19 or nominated under clause`
  line `(d) or clause (e) or clause (f) of that section] shall hold office during the pleasure of the authority`
  line `appointing or nominating him, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4, for ''The chairman and the vice-chairman'' (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `2. The words '', vice-chairman'' omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 12 (w.e.f. 15-6-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `5. The words, brackets and figures ''and in sub-section (5)'' omitted by Act 66 of 1988, s.12 (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
  line
  line `6. The words, brackets and figures ''of sub-section (1)'' omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 9 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 12, for certain words (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for ''four years'' (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
  line
  line `9. The words ''and thereafter until his successor shall have been duly elected'' omitted by Act 45 of 2006, s. 14`
  line `(w.e.f. 16-10-2006).`
  line
  line `10. The words ''or nominated'' omitted by Act 66 of 1988, s. 12 (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
  line
  line `11. The words ''or re nomination'' omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 12, for ''A director'' (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `16. The words ''and thereafter until his successor shall have been duly appointed or nominated'' omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 12`
  line `(w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 12, for certain words (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
  line
  line `19. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (35191)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Local Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35191&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Local Boards.--(1) There shall be constituted at each place where the State Bank has a local`
  line `head office, a Local Board which shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) the chairman, ex officio or the managing director nominated by the chairman;]`
  line
  line `^3[(b) all such directors elected or nominated to the Central Board under clause (c) or clause (d) of`
  line `section 19 as are ordinarily resident in the area falling within the jurisdiction of the local head office;]`
  line
  line `(c) six members to be nominated by the Central Government ^4***;`
  line
  line ^5*****
  line
  line `(e) ^6[the Chief General Manager] of the local head office, appointed by the State Bank, ex officio.`
  line
  line `^7[(2) Where as a result of the establishment of any local head office (hereinafter referred to as the new`
  line `local head office) for any area which is already falling within the jurisdiction of another local head office`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the existing local head office) a Local Board (hereinafter referred to as the new`
  line `Local Board) is constituted for the new local head office, any person who is, at the time of such`
  line `Constitution, holding office as a member of a Local Board (hereinafter referred to as the existing Local`
  line `Board) for an existing local head office under clause (c) of sub-section (1) and is ordinarily resident in the`
  line `area falling within the jurisdiction of the new local head office, shall cease to hold office as member of`
  line `the existing Local Board and shall become a member of the new Local Board and shall on becoming such`
  line `member be deemed to have been nominated to the new Local Board and shall hold office as such member`
  line `for the unexpired portion of his term of office as a member of the existing Local Board.]`
  line
  line `(3) Any vacancy caused in the existing Local Board as a result of any member thereof becoming a`
  line `member of the new Local Board under sub-section (2) shall be deemed to be a casual vacancy and be`
  line `filled in accordance with the provisions of section 25.`
  line
  line ^8*****
  line
  line `^9[(5) The ^10[Central Government] shall, in consultation with the chairman, appoint--`
  line
  line `(a) a member of a Local Board nominated under clause (c) of sub-section (1) to be the president`
  line `thereof; and`
  line
  line `(b) a member of a Local Board holding office under clause (b) or nominated under clause (c) of`
  line `that sub-section to be the vice-president thereof.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 1964, s. 5, for section 21 (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 13, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 10, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. The words ''in consultation with the Reserve Bank'' omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 13 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 10(w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 5, for ''the Secretary and Treasurer'' (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 10, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `8. Omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 27of 2010, s. 13, for ''Governor of the Reserve Bank'' (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (35192)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 26
  title `Term of office of members of Local Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35192&sectionno=21A&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Term of office of members of Local Board.--^2[(1) Subject to the provisions contained in`
  line `this section and in sub-section (2) of section 21, a member of a Local Board--`
  line
  line `(a) nominated under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 21 shall hold office for such term, not`
  line `exceeding three years, as the Central Government may specify in this behalf ^3***;`
  line
  line `(b) elected under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 21 shall hold office for three years and ^4***,`
  line
  line `and shall be eligible for re-nomination or re-election, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years.]`
  line
  line ^5*****
  line
  line `(3) A director of the Central Board becoming a member of a Local Board by virtue of the provisions`
  line `of clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 21 shall cease to hold office as such member on his ceasing to`
  line `be a director or on his ceasing to be ordinarily resident in the relevant area.`
  line
  line `(4) The president and the vice-president of a Local Board shall each hold office for two years or the`
  line `remaining period of his office as a member of the Local Board, whichever is shorter, and shall be eligible`
  line `for re-appointment so long as he is a member of the Local Board.`
  line
  line `^6[(5) A member of a Local Board nominated under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 21 shall`
  line `hold office during the pleasure of the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 1964, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 13, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The words ''and thereafter until his successor has been duly nominated'' omitted by Act 45 of 2006, s. 15 (w.e.f. 16-10-2006).`
  line
  line `4. The words ''and thereafter until his successor has been duly nominated'' omitted by Act 45 of 2006, s. 15 (w.e.f. 16-10-2006).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 11 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 13 (w.e.f. 8-7-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_b:
  sectionId (35193)
  sectionNo 21B
  orderNo 27
  title `Powers of Local Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 14, for section 21B (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35193&sectionno=21B&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[21B. Powers of Local Board.--In respect of the area falling within the jurisdiction of the local`
  line `head office for which the Local Board has been constituted, a Local Board shall, subject to such general`
  line `or special direction as the Central Board may give from time to time, exercise such powers and perform`
  line `such duties and functions as may be entrusted or delegated to it by the Central Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_c:
  sectionId (35194)
  sectionNo 21C
  orderNo 28
  title `Local Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35194&sectionno=21C&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_21_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) A Local Committee may be constituted by the Central Board for any`
  line `area and shall consist of such number of members as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The chairman or the managing director nominated by him shall be an ex officio member of every`
  line `such Local Committee.]`
  line
  line `(3) A Local Committee shall exercise such powers and perform such functions and duties as the`
  line `Central Board may confer on or assign to it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 1964, s.6 (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 15, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (35231)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 29
  title `Disqualifications for directorship of Central Board or membership of Local Boards or Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35231&sectionno=22&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be qualified to be a director of the Central Board or a member of a`
  line `Local Board or of a Local Committee if--`
  line
  line `(a) he holds the office of director, provisional director, promoter, agent or manager of any`
  line `banking company already established or advertised as about to be established; or`
  line
  line `(b) he is a salaried officer of Government not specially authorised by the Central Government to`
  line `be a director or member; or`
  line
  line `(c) he has been removed or dismissed from the service of Government on a charge of corruption`
  line `or bribery; or`
  line
  line `(d) he holds any office of profit under the State Bank other than the office of`
  line `chairman, ^1*** ^2[managing director] or ^3[^4[Chief General Manager or legal or technical adviser]]; or`
  line
  line `^5[(da) in the case of a director appointed under clause (ca) or clause (cb)`
  line `^6*** of section 19,--`
  line
  line `(i) he is not serving in the State Bank or has not been serving in it for a continuous period of`
  line `at least five years; and`
  line
  line `(ii) he is of such age that there is a likelihood of his attaining the age of superannuation`
  line `during his term of office as a director; or]`
  line
  line `(e) he is or at any time has been adjudicated an insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts`
  line `or has compounded with his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(f) he is declared lunatic or becomes of unsound mind; or`
  line
  line `(g) he is or has been convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `^7[(h) in the case of an elected director, he is not registered as a holder in his own right of`
  line `unencumbered shares in the State Bank, either as sole holder or as first named holder when jointly`
  line `held, of a nominal value of at least five thousand rupees.]`
  line
  line `(2) No two persons who are partners of the same firm or are directors of the same private company or`
  line `one of whom is an agent of the other or holds a power of attorney from a firm of which the other is a`
  line `partner may be directors of the Central Board or members of the same Local Board or Local Committee at`
  line `the same time.`
  line
  line `(3) The appointment, nomination or election as director or member of a Local Board or of a Local`
  line `Committee of any person who is a member of Parliament or the Legislature, of any State shall be void`
  line `unless within two months of the date of his appointment, nomination or election he ceases to be a member`
  line `of Parliament or the State Legislature, and if any director or member of a Local Board or of a Local`
  line `Committee is elected or nominated as a member of Parliament or any State Legislature, he shall cease to`
  line `be a director or member of the Local Board or of Local Committee as from the date of such election or`
  line `nomination, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^8[(4) In this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) “banking company” has the same meaning as in the ^9[Banking Regulation Act, 1949`
  line `(10 of 1949)];`
  line
  line `(b) “manager” means the chief executive officer, by whatever name called, of a Banking`
  line company;
  line
  line `(c) “private company” has the same meaning as in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)].`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word “vice-chairman” omitted by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 1959, s. 2, for “or managing director” (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 35 of 1964, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 7, for “secretary and treasurer” (w.e.f. 26-6-1974).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 7 (w.e.f. 26-6-1974).`
  line
  line `6. The words, brackets and figure “of sub-section (1)” omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 13 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 16, for clause (h) (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 26 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f. 28-8-1959).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 13, for “Banking Companies Act, 1949” (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (35196)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 30
  title `Vacation of office of directors, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35196&sectionno=23&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `If a director of the Central Board or a member of a Local`
  line `Board or a Local Committee--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 22; or`
  line
  line `(b) resigns his office by giving notice in writing under his hand, in the case of the ^1`
  line `[chairman ^2***`
  line `and amanaging director] to the Central Government and in the case of other directors or members of`
  line `Local Boards or Committees, to the Central Board, and the resignation is accepted; or`
  line
  line `(c) is absent without leave of the Central Board, the Local Board or the Local Committee of`
  line `which he is a director or member, as the case may be, for more than three consecutive meetings`
  line thereof;
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that nothing in clause (c) shall apply to the chairman in relation to his membership of a`
  line `Local Board or of a Local Committee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4, for “the chairman and vice-chairman” (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `2. The word “, vice-chairman” omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 17 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso added by Act 21 of 1957, s. 3 (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (35197)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 31
  title `Removal from office of directors, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35197&sectionno=24&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after consulting the`
  line `Reserve Bank, remove from office ^1[the chairman ^2*** or a managing director.]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government, ^4*** may remove from office any director ^5[appointed under clause (ca)`
  line `or clause (cb) or nominated under clause(d) ^6[of section 19] ^7[or any member of a Local Board nominated`
  line `under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 21] and ^8[appoint or nominate, as the case may be], in his`
  line `stead another person to fill the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(4) The shareholders, other than the ^9[Central Government], may, by a resolution passed by majority,`
  line `of the votes of such shareholders holding in the aggregate not less than one-half of the share capital held`
  line `by all such shareholders, remove any director elected under clause (c)`
  line `^10***of section 19 and elect in his`
  line `stead another person to fill the vacancy.`
  line
  line `^11* * * * *`
  line
  line `(6) No person shall be removed from his office under sub-section (1)`
  line `^12*** or sub-section (3) unless`
  line `he has been given an opportunity of showing cause against his removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4, for “the chairman or the vice-chaiman” ( w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line `2. The word “, vice-chairman” omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 18 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line `3. Omitted by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line `4. The words “after consulting the Reserve Bank,” omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 18 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 8, for “nominated under clause (d)” (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 14, for “sub-section (1) of section 19” (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 35 of 1964, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 8 for “nominate” (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 32 of 2007, s. 8, for “Reserve Bank” (w.e.f. 29-6-2007).`
  line `10. Certain words omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line `11. Omitted by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line `12. The words, bracket and figure “or sub-section (2)” omitted by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_a:
  sectionId (35198)
  sectionNo 24A
  orderNo 32
  title `Suppression of Central Board in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 19 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35198&sectionno=24A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[24A. Supersession of Central Board in certain cases.-- (1) Where the Central Government, on`
  line `the recommendation of the Reserve Bank is satisfied that in the public interest or for preventing the`
  line `affairs of the State Bank being conducted in a manner detrimental to the interest of the depositors or the`
  line `State Bank or for securing the proper management of the State Bank, it is necessary so to do, the Central`
  line `Government may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, by order, supersede the Central Board for a`
  line `period not exceeding six months as may be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of supersession of the Central Board may be extended from time to time, so,`
  line `however, that the total period shall not exceed twelve months.`
  line
  line `(2) On supersession of the Central Board under sub-section (1), the Central Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the Reserve Bank, appoint an Administrator (not being an officer of the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government) who has experience in law, finance, banking, economics or`
  line `accountancy, for such period as it may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may issue such directions to the Administrator as it may consider`
  line `necessary and the Administrator shall be bound to follow such directions.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, upon making the order of supersession of the`
  line `Central Board--`
  line
  line `(a) the chairman, managing director and other directors shall, as from the date of supersession,`
  line `vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, be exercised and discharged by or on behalf of the Central`
  line `Board, or by a resolution passed in the general meeting of the State Bank, shall, until the Central`
  line
  line `Board is reconstituted, be exercised and discharged by the Administrator appointed under`
  line `sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that the powers exercised by the Administrator shall be valid notwithstanding that such`
  line `power is also exercisable by a resolution passed in the general meeting of the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, constitute a committee of`
  line `three or more persons who have experience in law, finance, banking, economics or accountancy to assist`
  line `the Administrator in the discharge of his duties.`
  line
  line `(6) The committee shall meet at such times and places and observe such rules of procedure as may be`
  line `specified by the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) The salary and allowances of the Administrator and the members of the committee shall be such`
  line `as may be specified by the rules made under this Act and be payable by the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(8) On and before the expiration of two months before the expiry of the period of supersession of the`
  line `Central Board, the Administrator of the State Bank shall call the general meeting of the State Bank to`
  line `elect new directors and re-constitute the said Board.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any`
  line `contract, no person shall be entitled to claim any compensation for the loss or termination of his office on`
  line `supersession of the Central Board.`
  line
  line `(10) The Administrator appointed under sub-section (2) shall vacate office immediately after the`
  line `re-constitution of the Central Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (35199)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 33
  title `Casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35199&sectionno=25&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) If the chairman, ^2*** or a managing director is rendered incapable of`
  line `discharging his duties by reason of infirmity or otherwise or is absent on leave or otherwise in`
  line `circumstances not involving the vacation of his office, the Central Government may, in consultation with`
  line `the Reserve Bank, appoint another person to officiate in the vacancy.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Where any vacancy occurs before the expiry of the term of office of a director, other than the`
  line `Chairman, ^2*** or a managing director or ^4[a director appointed under clause (ca) or ^5[clause (cb) of`
  line `section 19 or of a member of a Local Board other than the Chief General Manager] the vacancy shall be`
  line filled--
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an elected director, by election; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a director nominated under clause (d) of section 19 or a member of a Local`
  line `Board nominated under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 21, by nomination ^6***:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the duration of the vacancy in the office of an elected director is likely to be less`
  line `than six months, the vacancy may be filled by the remaining directors] by co-opting a person not`
  line `disqualified under section 22.]`
  line
  line `(3) A person elected or nominated or co-opted, as the case may be, ^7[under sub-section (2)] shall hold`
  line `office for the unexpired portion of the term of his predecessor.`
  line
  line `^8[(4) Where any vacancy occurs before the expiry of the term of office of a director appointed under`
  line `clause (ca) or clause (cb) ^9*** of section 19, such vacancy shall be filled in accordance with the said`
  line `clause (ca) or as the case may be, clause (cb), and the director so appointed shall hold office for the period`
  line `specified under sub-section (3A) of section 20.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4, for sub-section (1) w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `2. The word “, vice-chairman” omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 20 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 35 of 1964, s. 9, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 15, for certain words, brackets, letters and figure (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. The words “in consultation with the Reserve Bank” omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 20 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 9, for “under this section” (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line
  line `9. The words, brackets and figure “by sub-section (1)” omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 15 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (35200)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 34
  title `Remuneration of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35200&sectionno=26&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sections 27,`
  line `28 and 29, the directors shall be paid such fees and allowances for attending the meetings of the Central`
  line `Board or of any of its Committees and for attending to any other work of the State Bank as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no fees shall be payable to a managing`
  line `director or any other director who is an officer of the Central Government or the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (35201)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers and remuneration of chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35201&sectionno=27&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairman shall preside at all meetings of the`
  line `Central Board and subject to such general or special directions as the Central Board may give, exercise all`
  line `such powers and do all such acts and things as may be exercised or done by the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) The chairman shall receive such salary, fees, allowances and perquisites ^1[as may be determined`
  line `by the Central Government].`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4, for certain words (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
