  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (35233)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 37
  title `Powers and remuneration of managing director .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35233&sectionno=29&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A managing director--`
  line
  line `(a) shall be a whole-time officer of the State Bank; ^1***`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the general control of the chairman ^2***, shall exercise such powers and perform`
  line `such duties as may be entrusted or delegated to him by the Central Board ^2[; and]`
  line
  line `^3[(c) when authorised by the chairman, shall preside at the meetings of the Central Board in his`
  line absence.]
  line
  line `(2) A managing director shall receive such salary and allowances ^4 [as may be determined by the`
  line `Central Government].`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word “and” omitted by Act 27 of 2010, s. 22 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `2. The words “and the vice-chairman” omitted by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 73 of 1976, s. 4, for certain words (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
  line
  line `5. The proviso omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-6-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (35203)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 38
  title `Executive and other committees of the Central Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35203&sectionno=30&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Central Board may constitute`
  line `such and so many committees, including an executive committee, of itself as it deems fit to exercise such`
  line `powers and perform such duties as may, subject to such conditions, if any, as the Central Board may`
  line `impose, be delegated to them by the Central Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (35204)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 39
  title `Meetings of the Central Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35204&sectionno=31&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Central Board shall meet at such time and place and`
  line `shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be`
  line `prescribed; and the meeting of the Central Board may be held by participation of the directors of the`
  line `Central Board through videoconferencing or such other electronic means, as may be prescribed, which are`
  line `capable of recording and recognising the participation of the directors and the proceedings of such`
  line `meetings are capable of being recorded and stored:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may in consultation with the Reserve Bank, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, specify the matters which shall not be discussed in a meeting of the Central Board`
  line `held through videoconferencing or such other electronic means.`
  line
  line `(2) All questions at the meeting shall be decided by a majority of the votes of the directors present in`
  line `the meeting or through videoconferencing or such other electronic means and in the case of equality of`
  line `votes the chairman or, in his absence, the managing director authorised by the chairman shall have a`
  line `second or casting vote.]`
  line
  line `(3) A director who is directly or indirectly concerned or interested in any contract, loan, arrangement`
  line `or proposal entered into or proposed to be entered into by or on behalf of the State Bank shall at the`
  line `earliest possible opportunity disclose the nature of his interest to the Central Board and shall not be`
  line `present at any meeting of the Central Board when any such contract, loan, arrangement or proposal is`
  line `discussed unless his presence is required by the other directors for the purpose of eliciting information,`
  line `and no director so required to be present shall vote on any such contract, loan, arrangement or proposal.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to such director by reason only of his`
  line being--
  line
  line `(i) a shareholder (other than a director) holding not more than two per cent. of the paid-up capital`
  line `in any public company as defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or any corporation`
  line `established by or under any law for the time being in force in India or any co-operative society with`
  line `which or to which the State Bank has entered into or made, or proposes to enter into or make, a`
  line `contract, loan, arrangement or proposal; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a director ex officio of the State Bank ^3***, ^4[or]]`
  line
  line `^5[(iii) an officer or other employee of the State Bank, if he is a director appointed under`
  line `clause(ca) or clause (cb)`
  line `^6*** of section 19.]`
  line
  line `(4) If for any reason neither the chairman nor the vice-chairman is able to be present at a meeting of`
  line `the Central Board, any director, ^7***authorised by the chairman in writing in this behalf, and in the`
  line `absence of such authorisation,^8[any director] elected by the directors present from amongst themselves,`
  line `shall preside at the meeting and, in the event of equality of votes, shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 23, for sub-section (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 56 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-1963).`
  line
  line `3. The words “or a director of a subsidiary bank” omitted by Act 19 of 2018, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line
  line `4. Added by Act 48 of 1973, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-6-1976).`
  line
  line `6. The words, brackets and figure “of sub-section (1)” omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 16 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `7. The words “, other than a managing director” omitted by Act 48 of 1973, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for “any such director” (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (35205)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 40
  title `Meetings of Local Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35205&sectionno=31A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Meetings of Local Boards.-- (1) A Local Board shall meet at such time and place and shall`
  line `observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) All questions at the meeting shall be decided by a majority of the votes of the members present`
  line `and in the case of equality of votes, the person presiding at the meeting shall have a second or casting`
  line vote.
  line
  line `(3) A member who is directly or indirectly concerned or interested in any contract, loan, arrangement`
  line `or proposal entered into or proposed to be entered into by or on behalf of the State Bank, shall, at the`
  line `earliest possible opportunity, disclose the nature of his interest to the Local Board and shall not be present`
  line `at any meeting of the Local Board when any such contract, loan, arrangement or proposal is discussed`
  line `unless his presence is required by the other members for the purpose of eliciting information, and no`
  line `member so required to be present shall vote on any such contract, loan, arrangement or proposal:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to such member by reason only of his`
  line being--
  line
  line `(i) a shareholder (other than a director) holding not more than two per cent. of the paid-up capital`
  line `in any public company as defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or any corporation`
  line `established by or under any law for the time being in force in India or any co-operative society, with`
  line `which or to which the State Bank has entered into or made or proposes to enter into or make, a`
  line `contract, loan, arrangement or proposal; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a director ex officio of the State Bank ^2***.`
  line
  line `(4) If for any reason neither the president nor the vice-president is able to be present at a meeting of`
  line `the Local Board, any member, ^3[other than the Chief General Manager] elected by the members present`
  line `from amongst themselves, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the chairman shall preside at any meeting of a`
  line `Local Board at which he is present and in the absence of the chairman, ^4[the managing director authorised`
  line `by the chairman], shall, whenever he is present, preside at such meetings.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 1964, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-2-1964).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or a director of a subsidiary bank" omitted by Act 19 of 2018, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 11, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-7-1974).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 24, for "the vice-chairman, if he is a member of the Local Board" (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (35206)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 41
  title `State Bank to act as agent of the Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35206&sectionno=32&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Bank shall, if so required, by`
  line `the Reserve Bank, act as agent of the Reserve Bank at all places in India where it has a branch ^1*** and`
  line `where there is no branch of the banking department of the Reserve Bank, for--`
  line
  line `(a) paying, receiving, collecting and remitting money, bullion and securities on behalf of any`
  line `Government in India; and`
  line
  line `(b) undertaking and transacting any other business which the Reserve Bank may from time to`
  line `time entrust to it.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions on which any such agency business shall be carried on by the State`
  line `Bank on behalf of the Reserve Bank shall be such as may be agreed upon.`
  line
  line `(3) If no agreement can be reached on any matter referred to in sub-section (2) or if a dispute arises`
  line `between the State Bank and the Reserve Bank as to the interpretation of any agreement between them, the`
  line `matter shall be referred to the Central Government and the decision of the Central Government thereon`
  line `shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Bank may transact any business or perform any functions entrusted to it under`
  line `sub-section (1) ^2[by itself ^3***] or through an agent approved by the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words “or where there is a branch of a subsidiary bank” omitted by Act 19 of 2018, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1954, s. 64 and the Third Schedule, for “either by itself” (w.e.f. 10-9-1959).`
  line
  line `3. The words “or through a subsidiary bank” omitted by Act 19 of 2018, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (35207)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 42
  title `Other business which the State Bank may transact.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 12, for section 33 (w.e.f. 1-3-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35207&sectionno=33&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1[33. Other business which the State Bank may transact.-- Subject to the other provisions`
  line `contained in this Act, the State Bank may carry on and transact the business of banking as defined in`
  line `clause (b) of section 5 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), and may engage in one or more`
  line `of the other forms of business specified in sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (35208)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 43
  title `Business which the State Bank may not transact.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35208&sectionno=34&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1***(6) Save as otherwise provided in ^2[this Act] the State Bank shall not own or, acquire any ^3*** immovable property except for the purpose of providing buildings or other accomodation in which to`
  line `carry on the business of the State Bank or for providing residences for its officers and other employees:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such building or other accommodation is not immediately required for any of the`
  line `purposes of the State Bank, the State Bank may utilise it to the best advantage by letting it out or in any`
  line `other manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-sections (1), (2), (3) or (5) omitted by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-3-1977).Earlier sub-section (3) was substituted for sub-sections`
  line `(3) or (4) by Act 29 of 1959, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-3-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 56 of 1962, s.2, for "section 33" (w.e.f. 1-1-1963).`
  line
  line `3. The words "interest in" omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (35209)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 44
  title `State Bank may acquire the business of other Banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35209&sectionno=35&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Bank may, with the`
  line `sanction of the Central Government, and shall, if so directed by the Central Government in consultation`
  line `with the Reserve Bank, enter into negotiations for acquiring the business, including the assets and`
  line `liabilities, of any banking institution.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The terms and conditions relating to such acquisition, if agreed upon by the Central Board of the`
  line `State Bank and the directorate or management of the banking institution concerned and approved by the`
  line `Reserve Bank, shall be submitted to the Central Government for its sanction and that Government may by`
  line `order in writing (hereafter in this section referred to as the order of sanction) accord its sanction thereto.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force or any`
  line `instrument regulating the constitution of the banking institution concerned, the terms and conditions as`
  line `sanctioned by the Central Government shall come into effect on the date specified by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf in the order of sanction and be binding upon the State Bank and the banking`
  line `institution concerned as well as upon the shareholders (or, as the case may be, proprietors) and creditors`
  line `of that banking institution.`
  line
  line `(4) If for any reason the terms and conditions cannot come into effect on the date specified in the`
  line `order of sanction, the Central Government may fix another suitable date for that purpose.`
  line
  line `(5) On the date on which the terms and conditions as aforesaid come into effect the business and the`
  line `assets and liabilities of the banking institution concerned as covered by the acquisition shall, by virtue,`
  line `and in accordance with the provisions, of the order of sanction stand transferred to, and become`
  line `respectively the business and the assets and liabilities of, the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(6) The consideration for the acquisition of the business and the assets and liabilities of any banking`
  line `institution under this section may, if so agreed upon, be paid either in cash or by allotment of shares in the`
  line `capital of the State Bank or partly in cash and partly by allotment of shares, and the State Bank may, for`
  line `the purpose of any such allotment, increase, subject to the other provisions contained in this Act relating`
  line `to the increase of capital, the capital of the State Bank by the issue of such number of shares as may be`
  line `determined by the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(7) Any business acquired under this section shall thereafter be carried on by the State Bank in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, subject to such exemptions or modifications as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make in this behalf in consultation with the`
  line `Reserve Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such exemption or modification shall be made so as to have effect for a period of`
  line `more than seven years from the date of acquisition.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law or in any agreement for the time being in force, on the acquisition of the business and the assets`
  line `and liabilities of any banking institution under this section, no officer or other employee of that banking`
  line `institution shall be entitled to any compensation to which he may be entitled under that Act or that other`
  line `law or that agreement and no claim in respect of such compensation shall be entertained by any Court,`
  line `Tribunal or other authority, if on his having accepted in writing an offer of employment by the State Bank`
  line `on the terms and conditions proposed by it he has been employed in accordance with such terms and`
  line conditions.
  line
  line `(9) The Central Government may, if it considers necessary or expedient in the case of any banking`
  line `institution in relation to which an order of sanction has been made under this section, appoint whether`
  line `before or after the coming into effect of the terms and conditions relating to the acquisition of the business`
  line `and the assets and liabilities of that banking institution, a suitable person to take over the management of`
  line `that banking institution for the purposes of winding up its affairs and distributing its assets, and the`
  line `expenditure incurred in connection with such management (including the remuneration for the person so`
  line `appointed and his staff, if any) shall be paid out of the assets of the banking institution or by the State`
  line `Bank as the Central Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(10) Simultaneously with the appointment of a suitable person to take over the management of any`
  line `banking institution under sub-section (9) or immediately thereafter, the Central Government shall issue`
  line `directions to be followed by that person in the management of that banking institution for the purposes`
  line `aforesaid and thereupon--`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or the ^2[Banking Regulation Act, 1949`
  line `(10 of 1949),] or any other law for the time being in force or any instrument having effect by virtue of`
  line `any such Act or law, in so far as they are inconsistent with such directions, shall cease to apply to or`
  line `in relation to that banking institution;`
  line
  line `(b) all persons in charge of the management, including any person holding office as manager or`
  line `director of the banking institution immediately before the issue of such directions, shall be deemed to`
  line `have vacated their offices as such; and`
  line
  line `(c) the persons appointed to take over the management of the banking institution shall in`
  line `accordance with those directions take all such steps as may be necessary to facilitate the winding up`
  line `of its affairs and distribution of its assets.`
  line
  line `(11) The Central Government, when satisfied that nothing further remains to be done in order to wind`
  line `up the affairs of any such banking institution, may by another order in writing direct that as from such`
  line `date as may be specified therein the banking institution shall stand dissolved and thereupon any such`
  line `direction shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law.`
  line
  line `(12) No action under this section shall be questioned on the ground merely of any defect in the`
  line `constitution of any banking institution in relation to which such action has been taken or in the`
  line `constitution of its Board of Directors or in the appointment of any person entrusted with the management`
  line `of its affairs.`
  line
  line `(13) In this section "banking institution" includes any individual or any association of individuals`
  line `(whether incorporated or not, or whether a department of Government or a separate institution), carrying`
  line `on the business of banking.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1959, s. 6, for sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) (w.e.f. 28-8-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 17, for "Banking Companies Act, 1949" (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_a:
  sectionId (35210)
  sectionNo 35A
  orderNo 45
  title `Arrangement with the State Bank on appointment of directors to prevail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 43 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35210&sectionno=35A&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[35A. Arrangement with the State Bank on appointment of directors to prevail.-- (1) Where any`
  line `arrangement entered into by the State Bank with a company provides for the appointment by the State`
  line `Bank of one or more directors of such company, such provisions and any appointment of directors made`
  line `in pursuance thereof shall be valid and effective notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in any other law for the time being in force or in the memorandum,`
  line `articles of association or any other instrument relating to the company, and any provision regarding share`
  line `qualification, age limit, number of directorships, removal from office of directors and such like conditions`
  line `contained in any such law or instrument aforesaid, shall not apply to any director appointed by the State`
  line `Bank in pursuance of the arrangement as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) Any director appointed as aforesaid shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office during the pleasure of the State Bank and may be removed or substituted by any`
  line `person by order in writing of the State Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) not incur any obligation or liability by reason only of his being a director or for anything done`
  line `or omitted to be done in good faith in the discharge of his duties as a director or anything in relation`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(c) not be liable to retirement by rotation and shall not be taken into account for computing the`
  line `number of directors liable to such retirement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (35211)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 46
  title `Integration and Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35211&sectionno=36&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Bank shall maintain a special fund to be`
  line `known as the Integration and Development Fund into which shall be paid--`
  line
  line `(a) the dividends payable to the ^1[Central Government] on such shares of the State Bank held by`
  line `it as do not exceed fifty-five per cent. of the total issued capital; and`
  line
  line `(b) such contributions as the ^2*** the Central Government may make from time to time.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that if the balance in the Integration and Development Fund on the date of declaration of`
  line `any dividends by the State Bank is rupees five crores or more, no amount shall be paid into that Fund`
  line `under clause (a) and the dividends payable to the ^1[Central Government] shall be ^4[paid to that`
  line `Government], and if such balance on such date is less than rupees five crores, only so much of dividends`
  line `then payable as will bring such balance to rupees five crores shall be paid into that Fund and the balance`
  line `of such dividends shall be paid to the ^1[Central Government].]`
  line
  line `(2) The amount in the said Fund shall be applied exclusively for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) losses in excess of such yearly sum as may be agreed upon between the ^1[Central`
  line `Government] and the State Bank and attributable to the branches established in pursuance of`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 16; ^5***`
  line
  line `^6* * * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) such other losses or expenditure as may be approved by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the said Fund shall be the property, of the ^1[Central`
  line `Government] and no shareholder of the State Bank or any other person shall have any claim to the amount`
  line `held in the said Fund.`
  line
  line `^7[(4) No amount applied for any of the purposes specified in sub-section (2) shall, for the purposes of`
  line `the ^8[Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961)], be treated as income, profits or gains of the State Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2007, s. 9, for “Reserve Bank” (w.e.f. 29-6-2007).`
  line `2. The words “the Reserve Bank or” omitted by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-6-2007).`
  line `3. The proviso added by Act 35 of 1964, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2007, s. 9, for “paid to that Bank” (w.e.f. 29-6-2007).`
  line `5. The word “and” omitted by Act 38 of 1959, s. 64 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 10-9-1959).`
  line `6. Clause (aa) omitted by Act 19 of 2018, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 26 of 1959, s. 7 (w.e.f. 28-8-1959).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 18, for “Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922)” (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (35212)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 47
  title `Reserve Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35212&sectionno=37&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The State Bank shall establish a Reserve Fund which shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount held in the Reserve Fund of the Imperial Bank transferred to the State Bank on the`
  line `appointed day; and`
  line
  line `(b) such further sums as may be transferred to it by the State Bank out of its annual net profits`
  line `before declaring a dividend.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (35213)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 48
  title `Disposal of profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35213&sectionno=38&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) After making provision for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation in`
  line `assets, equalisation of dividends, contribution to staff and superannuation funds and for all other matters`
  line `for which provisions is necessary by or under this Act or which are usually provided for by banking`
  line `companies, the State Bank may, out of its net profits, declare a dividend.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of paragraph 6 of the First Schedule, the rate of dividend shall be`
  line `determined by the Central Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38_a:
  sectionId (35214)
  sectionNo 38A
  orderNo 49
  title `Transfer of unpaid or unclaimed dividend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 25 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35214&sectionno=38A&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Transfer of unpaid or unclaimed dividend.-- (1) Where, after the commencement of the`
  line `State Bank of India (Amendment) Act, 2010 (27 of 2010), a dividend has been declared by the State Bank`
  line `but which has not been paid to a shareholder or claimed by any shareholder entitled to it, within thirty`
  line `days from the date of declaration, the State Bank shall, within seven days from the date of expiry of the`
  line `said period of thirty days, transfer the total amount of dividend which remains unpaid, or unclaimed, to a`
  line `special account to be named, the "unpaid dividend account" maintained by it.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this sub-section, the expression "dividend which remains unpaid" means any`
  line `dividend the warrant in respect thereof has not been encashed or which has otherwise not been paid or`
  line claimed.
  line
  line `(2) Where the whole or any part of any dividend, declared by the State Bank before the`
  line `commencement of the State Bank of India (Amendment) Act, 2010 (27 of 2010), remains unpaid at such`
  line `commencement, the State Bank shall, within a period of six months from such commencement, transfer`
  line `such unpaid amount to the account referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Any money transferred to the unpaid dividend account of the State Bank, in pursuance of this`
  line `section which remains unpaid or unclaimed for a period of seven years from the date of such transfer shall`
  line `be transferred by the State Bank to the Investor Education and Protection Fund established under subsection (1) of section 205C of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) for being utilised for the purpose and`
  line `in the manner specified in that section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (35215)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 50
  title `Books to be balanced each year.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35215&sectionno=39&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The Central Board shall cause the books of the State Bank to`
  line `be closed, and balanced ^1[as] on the 31st day of ^2[March] ^3[or such other date in each year as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify:]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that with a view to facilitating the transition from one period of accounting to`
  line `another period of accounting under this section, the Central Government may, by order published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make such provisions as it considers necessary or expedient for the closing and`
  line `balancing of, or for other matters relating to, the books in respect of the concerned years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 14 (w.e.f. 31-12-1973).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 26, for “December” (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 14, for “in each year” (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `4. The proviso ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (35216)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 51
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35216&sectionno=40&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Bank shall furnish to the Central Government and to the Reserve Bank`
  line `^1[within three months from the 31st day of ^2[March] ^3[or the date specified under section 39, as the case`
  line `may be] as on which its books are closed and balanced]; its balance sheet, together with the profit and loss`
  line `account and the ^4[auditor’s report and a report by the Central Board on the working and activities of the`
  line `State Bank] during the period covered by the accounts:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the Reserve Bank, extend the`
  line `said period of three months by such further period, not exceeding three months, as it may think fit.]`
  line
  line `^6[(2) The balance sheet and the profit and loss account shall be signed by the chairman, managing`
  line `directors and at least three other directors of the Central Board.]`
  line
  line `(3) The State Bank shall also, within two months from the date on which its accounts are closed and`
  line `balanced, transmit to the Central Government and the Reserve Bank a statement showing, as far as may`
  line `be available, the name, address and occupation of, and the number of shares held by, each shareholder of`
  line `the State Bank as on the said date.`
  line
  line `^7[(4) The Central Government shall cause the auditors’ report and the report by the Central Board on`
  line `the working and activities of the State Bank to be laid, as soon as may be after they are received, before`
  line `each House of Parliament ^8***.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 15, for certain words (w.e.f. 31-12-1973).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 27, for “December” (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 15 (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 44, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `5. The proviso added by Act 48 of 1973, s. 15 (w.e.f. 31-12-1973).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 27, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 44 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `8. Certain words omitted by Act 81 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (35217)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 52
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35217&sectionno=41&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The affairs of the State Bank shall be ^1[audited by two or more auditors] duly`
  line `qualified to act as auditors of companies under ^2[section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)],`
  line `who shall be appointed by ^3[the State Bank with the previous approval of the Reserve Bank].`
  line
  line `(2) The auditors shall receive such remuneration as the Reserve Bank may fix in consultation with the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) An auditor may be a shareholder but not director or member of a Local Board or of a Local`
  line `Committee or an officer of the State Bank shall be eligible to be an auditor during his continuance in`
  line `office as such director, member or officer.`
  line
  line `(4) An auditor shall on relinquishing office, be eligible for reappointment.`
  line
  line `(5) The auditors shall severally be, and continue to act as, auditors until the ^4[annual] general meeting`
  line `after their respective appointment, and if any vacancy arises before the expiry of the term of office of an`
  line `auditor, the vacancy may be filled by ^3[the State Bank with the previous approval of the Reserve Bank].`
  line
  line `(6) Every auditor shall be supplied with a copy of the annual balance sheet and profit and loss`
  line `account, and a list of all books kept by the State Bank, and it shall be the duty of the auditor to examine`
  line `the balance sheet and profit and loss account with the accounts and vouchers relating thereto, and in the`
  line `performance of his duties, the auditor--`
  line
  line `(a) shall have, at all reasonable times, access to the books, accounts and other documents of the`
  line `State Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) may, at the expense of the State Bank, or if he is appointed by the Central Government, at the`
  line `expense of the Central Government, employ accountants or other persons to assist him in`
  line `investigating such accounts; and`
  line
  line `(c) may, in relation to such accounts, examine any director or any member of a Local Board or of`
  line `a Local Committee or any officer of the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(7) The auditors shall make a report to the Central Government upon the annual balance sheet and`
  line `accounts, and in every such report they shall state--`
  line
  line `(a) whether, in their opinion, the balance sheet is a full and fair balance sheet containing all the`
  line `necessary particulars and properly drawn up so as to exhibit ^5[a true and fair view] of the affairs of the`
  line `State Bank, and in case they have called for any explanation or information, whether it has been given`
  line `and whether it is satisfactory;`
  line
  line `(b) whether or not the transactions of the State Bank which have come to their notice have been`
  line `within the powers of the State Bank;`
  line
  line `(c) whether or not the returns received from the offices and branches of the State Bank have been`
  line `found adequate for the purpose of their audit;`
  line
  line `(d) whether the profit and loss account shows a true balance of ^6[profit or loss] for the period`
  line `covered by such account; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which they consider should be brought to the notice of the shareholders or`
  line `the Central Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^7[Explanation 1.-- For the purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the balance sheet shall not be treated as not disclosing a true and fair view of the affairs of`
  line `the State Bank, and`
  line
  line `(b) the profit and loss account shall not be treated as not showing a true balance of profit or`
  line `loss of the period covered by such account,`
  line
  line `merely, by reason of the fact that the balance sheet or, as the case may be, the profit and loss account,`
  line `does not disclose any matters which are, by the provisions of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949`
  line `(10 of 1949) read with the relevant provisions of this Act, not required to be disclosed.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of this Act, the accounts of the State Bank shall not be deemed`
  line `as having not been properly drawn up on the ground merely that they do not disclose certain matters`
  line if
  line
  line `(i) those matters are such as the State Bank is, by virtue of any provision contained in the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), read with the relevant provisions of this Act, or any`
  line `other Act, not required to disclose; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the provisions referred to in clause (i) are specified in the balance sheet and profit and loss`
  line `account of the State Bank or in the auditors report.`
  line
  line `(8) The auditors shall also forward a copy of the audit report to the State Bank.`
  line
  line `(9) Without prejudice to anything contained in the foregoing provisions, the Central Government may`
  line `appoint at any time such auditors as it thinks fit to examine and report on the accounts of the State Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 16, for "audited by two auditors (w.e.f. 31-12-1973).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 1959, s. 8, for "sub-section (1) of section 144 of the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913)"`
  line `(w.e.f. 28-8-1959).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 28, for "the Reserve Bank in consultation with the Central Government" (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 26 of 1959, s. 8, for "first" (w.e.f. 28-8-1959).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 35 of 1964, s. 13, for "a true and correct view" (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 26 of 1959, s. 8, for "profit and loss" (w.e.f. 28-8-1959).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 16 (w.e.f. 31-12-1973).`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (35218)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 53
  title `Balance sheet, etc., of State Bank may be discussed at general meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 29, for section 42 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35218&sectionno=42&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `^1[42. Balance sheet, etc., of State Bank may be discussed at general meeting.-- (1) An annual`
  line `general meeting shall be held in each financial year at the Corporate Centre or at such other place in`
  line `Mumbai other than the Corporate Centre or at such other place in India and at such time, as shall from`
  line `time to time be specified by the Central Board and a general meeting other than an annual general`
  line `meeting may be convened by the State Bank at any other time and at such place in India as shall from`
  line `time to time be specified by the Central Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that such annual general meeting shall be held before the expiry of six weeks from the date`
  line `on which the balance sheet together with the profit and loss account and auditors' report, under subsection (1) of section 40, is forwarded to the Central Government or to the Reserve Bank, whichever date`
  line `is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) The shareholders present at an annual general meeting shall be entitled to discuss and adopt the`
  line `balance sheet and the profit and loss account of the State Bank made up to the previous 31st day of March`
  line `or the date specified under section 39, as the case may be, the report of the Central Board on the working`
  line `and activities of the State Bank for the period covered by the accounts and the auditors' report on the`
  line `balance sheet and accounts.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (35219)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 54
  title `State Bank may appoint officers and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35219&sectionno=43&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The State Bank may appoint`
  line `such number of officers, advisers and employees as it considers necessary or desirable for the efficient`
  line `performance of its functions, and determine the terms and conditions of their appointment and service.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The officers, advisers and employees of the State Bank shall individually or jointly or with other`
  line `officers, advisers and employees in a Local Committee exercise such powers and perform such duties as`
  line `may by general or special order, be entrusted or delegated to them by the Central Board or its executive`
  line committee.]
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 43 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 35 of 1964, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 30, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_a:
  sectionId (35220)
  sectionNo 43A
  orderNo 55
  title Bonus.
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 64 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 11-9-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35220&sectionno=43A&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[43A. Bonus.-- (1) No officer, adviser or [other employee other than an employee within the`
  line `meaning of clause (13) of section 2 of the Payment of Bonus Act, 1965 (21 of 1965)] of the State Bank`
  line `shall be entitled to be paid any bonus.`
  line
  line `(2) No employee of the State Bank, being an employee within the meaning of clause (13) of section 2`
  line `of the Payment of Bonus Act, 1965 (21 of 1965), shall be entitled to be paid any bonus except in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of that Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall have effect notwithstanding any judgment, decree or order of`
  line `any Court, tribunal or other authority and notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of`
  line `this Act or in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or any other law for the time being in force`
  line `or any practice, usage or custom or any contract, agreement, settlement, award or other instrument.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (35221)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 56
  title `Obligation as to fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2005, s. 34 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 14-12-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35221&sectionno=44&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Bank shall observe, except as otherwise`
  line `required by law, the practices and usages customary among bankers, and, in particular, it shall not divulge`
  line `any information relating to or to the affairs of its constituents except in circumstances in which it is, in`
  line `accordance with the law or practice and usage customary among bankers, necessary or appropriate for the`
  line `State Bank to divulge such information.`
  line
  line `(2) Every director, member of a Local Board or of a Local Committee, auditor, adviser, officer or`
  line `other employee of the State Bank shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and`
  line `secrecy as in the form set out in the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `^1(3) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the credit information disclosed under the Credit`
  line `Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005 (30 of 2005).]`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (35222)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 57
  title `Bar to liquidation of State Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35222&sectionno=45&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the winding up of companies`
  line `shall apply to the State Bank, and the State Bank shall not be placed in liquidation save by order of the`
  line `Central Government and in such manner as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (35223)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 58
  title `Indemnity of directors and members of Local Boards and Local Committees, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35223&sectionno=46&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Every director and every member of a Local Board or a Local Committee shall be indemnified by the`
  line `State Bank against all losses and expenses incurred by him in or in relation to the discharge of his duties`
  line `except such as are caused by his own wilful act or default.`
  line
  line `(2) Neither a director nor a member of a Local Board or a Local Committee shall be responsible for`
  line `any loss or expense caused to the State Bank by the insufficiency or deficiency of the value of or title to`
  line `any property or security acquired or taken on behalf of the State Bank or by the insolvency or wrongful`
  line `act of any customer or debtor or by anything done in or in relation to the execution of the duties of his`
  line `office or otherwise than for his wilful act or default.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (35224)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 59
  title `Defects in appointment or constitution not to invalidate acts or proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35224&sectionno=47&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act or`
  line `proceeding of the Central Board or of a Local Board or a Local Committee shall be questioned on the`
  line `ground merely of the existence of any vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Board or Committee, as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) All acts done by any person acting in good faith as a director or as a member of a Local Board or`
  line `of a Local Committee shall, notwithstanding that there was some defect in his appointment or`
  line `qualifications, be as valid as if he was a director of the Central Board or a member of the Local Board or`
  line `the Local Committee, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (35234)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 60
  title `Omi tted .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35234&sectionno=48&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `[Power to remove difficulties] Omitted by the State Bank of India (Amendment) Act, 1964`
  line `(35 of 1964), s.15 (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (35235)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 61
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35235&sectionno=49&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, in consultation`
  line `with the Reserve Bank, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, ^1[make rules to provide for all matters`
  line `for which provision is necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line Act.]
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure for the payment of compensation under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the determination of persons to whom the said compensation shall be payable in all cases,`
  line `including cases where shares in the Imperial Bank have been held by more than one person, or where`
  line `they have been transferred before the appointed day but the transfer has not been registered or where`
  line `the shareholder is dead;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) the manner of appointment of a director under clause (ca) or clause (cb) ^3*** of section 19,`
  line `and all other matters connected therewith or incidental thereto;]`
  line
  line `^4[(d) the time and place of meeting of the Committee and the rules of procedure to be observed by`
  line `it under sub-section (6) of section 24A;`
  line
  line `(e) the salary and allowances of the Administrator and the members of the committee under`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 24A.]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 18, for certain words (w.e.f. 31-12-1973).`
  line
  line `2. The words, brackets and figure “of sub-section (1)” omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 19 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 18 (w.e.f. 31-12-1973).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 31 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 47 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (35226)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power of Central Board to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35226&sectionno=50&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Board may, after consultation`
  line `with the Reserve Bank and with the previous sanction of the Central Government ^1[by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette] make regulations, not inconsistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to`
  line `provide for all matters for which provision is expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature of shares of the State Bank, the manner in which and the conditions subject to`
  line `which shares may be held and transferred and generally all matters relating to the rights and duties of`
  line shareholders;
  line
  line `^2[(aa) the procedure for increasing issued capital by the issue of equity or preference shares under`
  line `sub-section (2) and the manner of accepting money for issued capital, forfeiture and re-issue of shares`
  line `under sub-section (5) , of section 5;`
  line
  line `(ab) the manner of nominating an individual by one individual under sub-section (1) , the manner`
  line `of nominating an individual by the joint holders under sub-section (2), the manner of varying or`
  line `cancellation of nomination under sub-section (3), and the manner of nominating a minor under`
  line `sub-section (4) , of section 10A;]`
  line
  line `^3[(b) the maintenance of register of shareholders, and the particulars to be entered in such register`
  line `in addition to those specified in section 13, the safeguards to be observed in the maintenance of`
  line `register of shareholders on computer ^4[floppies or diskettes or any other electronic form], the`
  line `inspection and closure of the register of shareholders and all other matters connected therewith;]`
  line
  line `(c) the holding and conduct of elections under this Act, including the allocation of elected`
  line `directors to the various areas ^5[falling within the jurisdiction of each local head office], and the final determination of doubts or disputes regarding the qualifications of candidates for election or`
  line `regarding the validity of elections;`
  line
  line `^6[(ca) the determination of areas falling within the jurisdiction of each local head office;]`
  line
  line `^7[(d) the powers, functions and duties of Local Boards and the restrictions, conditions or`
  line `limitations, if any, subject to which they may be exercised or performed, the formation and`
  line `constitution of Local Committees (including the number of members of any such Committee) and of`
  line `Committees of Local Boards, the powers, functions and duties of such Committees, the holding of`
  line `meetings of Local Committees and Committees of Local Boards and the conduct of business thereat;]`
  line
  line `(e) the fees and allowances which may be paid to directors, or members of Local Boards or Local`
  line `Committees for attending any meetings of the Central Board or of its committees or of the Local`
  line `Boards or Local Committees, as the case may be, or for attending to any other work of the State`
  line Bank;
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which the business of the Central Board ^8[or of Local Boards] shall be`
  line `transacted and the procedure to be followed at the meetings thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) the formation of committees of the Central Board and the delegation of powers and functions`
  line `of the Central Board to such committees and the conduct of business in such committees;`
  line
  line `^9* * * * *`
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which general meetings shall be convened, the procedure to be followed thereat`
  line `and the manner in which voting rights may be exercised;`
  line
  line `(j) the holding of meetings of shareholders ^10*** and the business to be transacted thereat;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which notices may be served on behalf of the State Bank upon shareholders or`
  line `other persons;`
  line
  line `(l) the provision of seals for the State Bank and the manner and effect of their use;`
  line
  line `(m) the conduct and defence of legal proceedings and the manner of signing pleadings;`
  line
  line `(n) the duties and conduct of officers, other employees, advisers and agents of the State Bank;`
  line
  line `^11[(o) the establishment and maintenance of superannuation pension, provident or other funds for`
  line `the benefit of the employees of the State Bank or of the dependants of such employees or for the`
  line `purposes of the State Bank, and the granting of superannuation allowances, annuities and pensions`
  line `payable out of any such fund;]`
  line
  line `(p) the form and manner in which contracts binding on the State Bank may be executed;`
  line
  line `^12[(q) the terms, conditions, stipulations, restrictions and limitations, if any, in the transaction by`
  line `the State Bank of its businesses in regard to the advancing or lending of money or the discounting or`
  line `purchase of any instrument, negotiable or otherwise, with or without reference to any security,`
  line `purpose, amount, period or otherwise;]`
  line
  line `(r) the conditions subject to which alone, advances may be made to directors, members of Local`
  line `Boards or of Local Committees or officers of the State Bank, or the relatives of such directors,`
  line `members or officers or to companies, firms or individuals with which or with whom such directors,`
  line `members, officers, or relatives, are connected as partners, directors, managers, servants, shareholders`
  line `or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(s) the statements, returns, and forms that are required for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(t) the payment of dividends, including interim dividends;`
  line
  line `(u) generally for the conduct of the business of the State Bank.`
  line
  line `^13[(2A) All regulations made under this section shall have effect from such earlier or later date as may`
  line `be specified in the regulations.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the first regulations shall be made by the`
  line `Reserve Bank with the previous sanction of the Central Government, and thereupon shall be deemed to be`
  line `the regulations made by the Central Board under this section and shall have force accordingly until they`
  line `are amended or repealed.`
  line
  line `^14[(4) Every regulation shall, as soon as may be after it is made under this Act by the Central Board, be`
  line `forwarded to the Central Government and that Government shall cause a copy of the same to be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days, which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 17 (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 32 (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 20, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 2010, s. 32,for “floppies or diskettes” (w.e.f. 15-9-2010).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 20, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 3 of 1994, s. 20 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 35 of 1964, s. 16, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `9. Omitted by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1964).`
  line
  line `10. The words “on branch registers” omitted by Act 3 of 1994, s. 20 (w.e.f. 15-10-1993).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 26 of 1959, s. 10, for clause (o) (w.e.f. 28-8-1959).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 19, for clause (q) (w.e.f. 31-12-1973).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 48 of 1973, s. 19 (w.e.f. 31-12-1973).`
  line
  line `14. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 48 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (35227)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 63
  title `Requirements of foreign law to be complied with in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1955, s. 5, for section 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1957).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520&sectionId=35227&sectionno=51&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00007_195523_1517807318520
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `^1[51. Requirements of foreign law to be complied within certain cases.--If, according to the laws`
  line `of any country outside India, the provisions of this Act by themselves are not effective to transfer to and`
  line `vest in the State Bank any asset or liability which forms part of the undertaking of the Imperial Bank and`
  line `which is situate in that country, the Imperial Bank shall take all such steps as may be required by the laws`
  line `of that country for the purpose of effecting or perfecting such transfer and vesting, and in connection`
  line `therewith the Imperial Bank may realise any asset and discharge any liability and transfer the net proceeds`
  line `thereof to the State Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (35236)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 64
  title `Omitte d .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
